results.name: Number of divisors k of n with gcd(k+1, n) = 1.
example: The positive divisors of 8 are 1, 2, 4 and 8. (2+1), (4+1) and (8+1) are relatively prime to 8, so a(8) = 3.
results.author: _Leroy Quet_, Aug 10 2000
